result.notes: North Yorkshire County Council maintains a Contract Register, the purpose of which is to record key details of all Contracts with an aggregate value of £25,000 or more (excluding those related to individual packages of care). This register will be published on a quarterly basis.

resources.description:
We publish details of our contracts register for items of spending which exceed £10,000 (excluding those related to individual packages of care). This register will be published on a quarterly basis.

We also publish details of framework agreements and approved lists which we have established; these may also be used by other public sector bodies. The estimated total value of the agreement/list shown covers expenditure by all participating bodies and may not reflect our spending. For details of our expenditure with these suppliers, please review the spending over £500 register above.
resources.name: Contracts over £10,000 and framework agreements as at 30th September 2014
